<%- include('../partials/header', { title: 'Terms of Use' }) %>

<!--
  Terms of Use

  Defines the rules and conditions for using the Quartier Bike ID service.
  This is a community project — terms are kept simple and fair.
-->
<main class="container py-4">
  <div class="row justify-content-center">
    <div class="col-12 col-md-10 col-lg-8">

      <h1 class="mb-4">Terms of Use</h1>
      <p class="text-muted">Last updated: <%= new Date().toLocaleDateString('en-GB', { year: 'numeric', month: 'long', day: 'numeric' }) %></p>

      <!-- ── 1. About the service ── -->
      <h2 class="h4 mt-4">1. About This Service</h2>
      <p>
        Quartier Bike ID is a <strong>free, non-commercial community project</strong>
        that helps neighbours register their bicycles with QR code labels.
        The service is operated by Guillermo Pomphile for the benefit of the
        local neighbourhood.
      </p>
      <p>
        By creating an account and using this service, you agree to these terms.
      </p>

      <!-- ── 2. Account registration ── -->
      <h2 class="h4 mt-4">2. Account Registration</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>You must provide a valid email address to create an account.</li>
        <li>You are responsible for keeping your login credentials secure.</li>
        <li>You may only register bicycles that you own.</li>
        <li>One account per person — do not create multiple accounts.</li>
        <li>You can delete your account at any time.</li>
      </ul>

      <!-- ── 3. Bicycle registration ── -->
      <h2 class="h4 mt-4">3. Bicycle Registration</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          You may register as many bicycles as you own under your account.
        </li>
        <li>
          The information you provide (brand, colour, photo) should be accurate
          to help identify your bicycle.
        </li>
        <li>
          Each bicycle receives a unique QR code. You are responsible for
          attaching the QR label to your bike.
        </li>
        <li>
          Do not upload inappropriate, offensive, or copyrighted images.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <!-- ── 4. Public scan page ── -->
      <h2 class="h4 mt-4">4. Public Scan Page</h2>
      <p>
        When someone scans your bike's QR code, they will see:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Your <strong>first name only</strong> (never your full name, email, or phone)</li>
        <li>Your bike's brand, colour, and description</li>
        <li>Your bike's photo (if uploaded)</li>
        <li>A contact form to send you a message</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        By registering a bike, you consent to this information being publicly
        visible to anyone who scans the QR code.
      </p>

      <!-- ── 5. Stolen bike reporting ── -->
      <h2 class="h4 mt-4">5. Stolen Bike Reporting</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          You may mark your bike as "stolen" if it has been stolen.
          <strong>Do not abuse this feature</strong> — false reports undermine the system.
        </li>
        <li>
          When a stolen bike is scanned, the finder may voluntarily share their
          GPS location with you. This is to help you locate your bike — not to
          identify, track, or confront the finder.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Always contact the police</strong> to report a stolen bike.
          This service is an aid, not a replacement for law enforcement.
        </li>
        <li>
          Never attempt to recover a stolen bike on your own in a way that
          could put you or others at risk.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <!-- ── 6. Garage parking ── -->
      <h2 class="h4 mt-4">6. Garage Parking</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          The garage parking contribution of <strong>CHF 40.00 per year per bike</strong>
          is voluntary and supports the maintenance of the shared garage.
        </li>
        <li>
          Payment is made via TWINT using the QR code provided with your bike label.
        </li>
        <li>
          The system tracks payment status for administrative purposes only.
          No payment or banking data is stored in the system.
        </li>
        <li>
          You may opt out of garage parking at any time by editing your bike settings.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <!-- ── 7. Contact form ── -->
      <h2 class="h4 mt-4">7. Contact Form</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          The contact form on the scan page allows anyone to send a message
          to the bike owner. Messages should be relevant to the bicycle
          (e.g., "I found your bike", "Your bike has a flat tyre").
        </li>
        <li>
          Do not use the contact form for spam, harassment, or commercial purposes.
        </li>
        <li>
          The operator reserves the right to delete abusive messages.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <!-- ── 8. Liability ── -->
      <h2 class="h4 mt-4">8. Limitation of Liability</h2>
      <p>
        This service is provided <strong>"as is" without warranty</strong>.
        The operator:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          Does not guarantee the service will be available at all times.
          The server runs on home infrastructure and may experience downtime.
        </li>
        <li>
          Is not responsible for any loss, damage, or theft of bicycles.
          The service aids identification but cannot prevent theft.
        </li>
        <li>
          Is not responsible for the accuracy of GPS location data shared
          by finders, or for any actions taken based on that data.
        </li>
        <li>
          Is not responsible for the content of messages sent through the
          contact form.
        </li>
        <li>
          Reserves the right to discontinue the service at any time, with
          reasonable notice to registered users.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <!-- ── 9. Acceptable use ── -->
      <h2 class="h4 mt-4">9. Acceptable Use</h2>
      <p>You agree not to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Register bicycles you do not own</li>
        <li>File false stolen reports</li>
        <li>Attempt to access other users' accounts or data</li>
        <li>Use the service for any illegal purpose</li>
        <li>Attempt to disrupt or overload the service</li>
        <li>Scrape, crawl, or automated access the service</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        The operator may suspend or delete accounts that violate these terms.
      </p>

      <!-- ── 10. Changes ── -->
      <h2 class="h4 mt-4">10. Changes to These Terms</h2>
      <p>
        These terms may be updated occasionally. Continued use of the service
        after changes constitutes acceptance. For significant changes,
        registered users will be notified by email.
      </p>

      <!-- ── 11. Governing law ── -->
      <h2 class="h4 mt-4">11. Governing Law</h2>
      <p>
        These terms are governed by <strong>Swiss law</strong>.
        Any disputes shall be resolved in the courts of the canton
        where the operator resides.
      </p>

      <!-- ── 12. Contact ── -->
      <h2 class="h4 mt-4">12. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        For questions about these terms, see the <a href="/imprint">Imprint</a>
        page for contact information.
      </p>

    </div>
  </div>
</main>

<%- include('../partials/footer') %>
